Goal
----
Validate the system behaves correctly for common flows: onboarding, deposits, withdrawals, transfers, and audit trail.

Scenario A — New customer + checking
-----------------------------------
Inputs

name: Jordan Lee
PIN: 1234
open checking

Expected
--------
customer ID generated
checking account number generated
balance starts at 0.00

Scenario B — Deposit and withdraw
---------------------------------
Actions

deposit 200.00
withdraw 50.00

Expected
--------
balance = 150.00
two transactions recorded:
DEPOSIT 200.00
WITHDRAW 50.00

Scenario C — Invalid withdrawal
-------------------------------
Action

withdraw 1000.00 (balance is 150.00)

Expected
--------
operation rejected (InsufficientFunds)
balance unchanged
no transaction recorded for failed operation

Scenario D — Transfer to savings
-------------------------------
Actions

open savings
transfer 25.00 from checking → savings

Expected
--------
checking balance = 125.00
savings balance = 25.00

transfer recorded in both accounts’ histories (or one shared record if you design it that way)
